messages.content: What does the Ontario building code requires when it comes to spacing between electrical outlets in residential dwellings

The Ontario Electrical Safety Code (OESC) regulation, updated in 2024 and effective as of May 1, 2025, includes the Canadian Electrical Code, Part I, with Ontario-specific amendments [esasafe](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEN8SFoG9M8xUyJh_tSLeJqQ1nS9mwWZe1Z0HcAyYGK3JdVNWc1ONRA5X7e35ibStsWRFdcx9JU1ZOGkmJvla_rULrZYc7X4PE5ftQU59LwWYLI_prCtfA6AA==) [newswire](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHhWDTIcvXEgr_KTbY1tJvV6E_RllScoOa0XCxpbBbiTEZYDi-kn_3kZw9jCGBUCULcMpOZLF941VjvPWeD3xOvAlnAwwcuLPvUYt3OEkf-kpP6lNKQ9T4J_q3wk9bG5IxtmfKMWf4Txz_SCf6Zq73uk-FxqKBDFTmUda2LNSvDDI4g4RzUZLO2pxFfj8rtXmFiub1oXHj1SCOf3tQ38kLDVBzQTQ==). Here's what it generally requires for electrical outlet spacing in residential dwellings:

*   **General Areas:** In living rooms, family rooms, bedrooms, and hallways, receptacle outlets must be installed so that no point along the floor line of any wall space is more than 1.8 meters (6 feet) horizontally from an outlet [thespruce](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDCWIOy6cxvblKtIpE9pONGHSz1cbaa__xWh4ixFWt8d1-ZztlJSRx2S-zR29B5DfSRmAc5MeqcTN3BSPodqwz6GQC_zNwsm35S-BtJ82hlm8sU_S2zeutUsVpix4fEletfjhxpBb3Wy304xIRnAFJSJdpEJrME0U=) [strathcona](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHV8AaxwyWwVMBXe7wtBt0t2EGcnjsvry1BlUlz3pgxystNGp-S-6zZK68naFcXb9xislQi2b5OIR1aXi3MH2ibC7TdthCcXQmpn_vqf3rPwTS5TyAVZSJWjZ9s4bGhfNtPloitKjIr58Ay9J9SACFVBYfY8lPmxi_6h1PZT-alFxDqpr8N2qd3Vuggr-hq9HTlhwRzajnxoC71cGg=) [nachi](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH21couP6GXkRyyXNdy96vcVbzjQmZWeia4u9rVoAngUmqtS7DDRFWldl2qOVNAzoKIuJB5oVnHIiqAmG-c2OJaIH0mc31nGuIPDuW9DgKmuSq9yQuYWqtnX2V-eF-5VODbcJqss7DeauAkpCU470QXLHzSchegmDue). This applies to wall spaces of 900 mm (3 feet) or more in width, excluding doorways, windows extending to the floor, fireplaces, and other permanent installations [strathcona](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHV8AaxwyWwVMBXe7wtBt0t2EGcnjsvry1BlUlz3pgxystNGp-S-6zZK68naFcXb9xislQi2b5OIR1aXi3MH2ibC7TdthCcXQmpn_vqf3rPwTS5TyAVZSJWjZ9s4bGhfNtPloitKjIr58Ay9J9SACFVBYfY8lPmxi_6h1PZT-alFxDqpr8N2qd3Vuggr-hq9HTlhwRzajnxoC71cGg=). An outlet is not required for walls less than 24 inches wide [thespruce](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDCWIOy6cxvblKtIpE9pONGHSz1cbaa__xWh4ixFWt8d1-ZztlJSRx2S-zR29B5DfSRmAc5MeqcTN3BSPodqwz6GQC_zNwsm35S-BtJ82hlm8sU_S2zeutUsVpix4fEletfjhxpBb3Wy304xIRnAFJSJdpEJrME0U=]. Hallways exceeding 10 feet in length must have at least one electrical outlet [thespruce](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDCWIOy6cxvblKtIpE9pONGHSz1cbaa__xWh4ixFWt8d1-ZztlJSRx2S-zR29B5DfSRmAc5MeqcTN3BSPodqwz6GQC_zNwsm35S-BtJ82hlm8sU_S2zeutUsVpix4fEletfjhxpBb3Wy304xIRnAFJSJdpEJrME0U=).
*   **Kitchens:** Outlets should be spaced no more than 1.2 meters (48 inches) apart, ensuring no point on the countertop is more than 610 mm (24 inches) from a receptacle [thespruce](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDCWIOy6cxvblKtIpE9pONGHSz1cbaa__xWh4ixFWt8d1-ZztlJSRx2S-zR29B5DfSRmAc5MeqcTN3BSPodqwz6GQC_zNwsm35S-BtJ82hlm8sU_S2zeutUsVpix4fEletfjhxpBb3Wy304xIRnAFJSJdpEJrME0U=) [nachi](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH21couP6GXkRyyXNdy96vcVbzjQmZWeia4u9rVoAngUmqtS7DDRFWldl2qOVNAzoKIuJB5oVnHIiqAmG-c2OJaIH0mc31nGuIPDuW9DgKmuSq9yQuYWqtnX2V-eF-5VODbcJqss7DeauAkpCU470QXLHzSchegmDue). Any countertop 305 mm (12 inches) wide or more should have an outlet on the wall behind it [thespruce](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDCWIOy6cxvblKtIpE9pONGHSz1cbaa__xWh4ixFWt8d1-ZztlJSRx2S-zR29B5DfSRmAc5MeqcTN3BSPodqwz6GQC_zNwsm35S-BtJ82hlm8sU_S2zeutUsVpix4fEletfjhxpBb3Wy304xIRnAFJSJdpEJrME0U=]. Outlets should not be higher than 508 mm (20 inches) above countertops [thespruce](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDCWIOy6cxvblKtIpE9pONGHSz1cbaa__xWh4ixFWt8d1-ZztlJSRx2S-zR29B5DfSRmAc5MeqcTN3BSPodqwz6GQC_zNwsm35S-BtJ82hlm8sU_S2zeutUsVpix4fEletfjhxpBb3Wy304xIRnAFJSJdpEJrME0U=]. It is recommended to have a dedicated counter receptacle for every 914 mm (3 feet) of usable counter space [multitradebuildingservices](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHmZ2egJp7ymMnCwQl5ZwnMh46PEv483LbwHH_WFZyhzlFP2Xa4BlxpmI4v82A5jre2ocX79LkZt_tpoZ6I-E5drZVtELc3Av-sPTqfgGjUf5DNsjGAvZ_jNCBj91tZ0o2XxNqcUCK3OccjQqNuePR5ColTTPo_M1cn0pFnYauhPxxz-hvI5JLGdfxk4cVK3B1FhEQ6LwQYe8zESw==).
*   **Bathrooms:** A ground fault circuit interrupter (GFCI) is required for outlets within 1.5 meters of a water source [multitradebuildingservices](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHmZ2egJp7ymMnCwQl5ZwnMh46PEv483LbwHH_WFZyhzlFP2Xa4BlxpmI4v82A5jre2ocX79LkZt_tpoZ6I-E5drZVtELc3Av-sPTqfgGjUf5DNsjGAvZ_jNCBj91tZ0o2XxNqcUCK3OccjQqNuePR5ColTTPo_M1cn0pFnYauhPxxz-hvI5JLGdfxk4cVK3B1FhEQ6LwQYe8zESw==]. A GFCI-protected receptacle must be within 1 meter (39 inches) of the wash basin [strathcona](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHV8AaxwyWwVMBXe7wtBt0t2EGcnjsvry1BlUlz3pgxystNGp-S-6zZK68naFcXb9xislQi2b5OIR1aXi3MH2ibC7TdthCcXQmpn_vqf3rPwTS5TyAVZSJWjZ9s4bGhfNtPloitKjIr58Ay9J9SACFVBYfY8lPmxi_6h1PZT-alFxDqpr8N2qd3Vuggr-hq9HTlhwRzajnxoC71cGg=) [multitradebuildingservices](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHmZ2egJp7ymMnCwQl5ZwnMh46PEv483LbwHH_WFZyhzlFP2Xa4BlxpmI4v82A5jre2ocX79LkZt_tpoZ6I-E5drZVtELc3Av-sPTqfgGjUf5DNsjGAvZ_jNCBj91tZ0o2XxNqcUCK3OccjQqNuePR5ColTTPo_M1cn0pFnYauhPxxz-hvI5JLGdfxk4cVK3B1FhEQ6LwQYe8zESw==]. Receptacles cannot be located within 500 mm of a bathtub or shower. Receptacles located 500 mm to 1 m from a bathtub or shower must be of a Class A type [strathcona](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHV8AaxwyWwVMBXe7wtBt0t2EGcnjsvry1BlUlz3pgxystNGp-S-6zZK68naFcXb9xislQi2b5OIR1aXi3MH2ibC7TdthCcXQmpn_vqf3rPwTS5TyAVZSJWjZ9s4bGhfNtPloitKjIr58Ay9J9SACFVBYfY8lPmxi_6h1PZT-alFxDqpr8N2qd3Vuggr-hq9HTlhwRzajnxoC71cGg=].
*   **Other locations**: Exterior plugs should be GFCI-protected and have weatherproof covers [multitradebuildingservices](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHmZ2egJp7ymMnCwQl5ZwnMh46PEv483LbwHH_WFZyhzlFP2Xa4BlxpmI4v82A5jre2ocX79LkZt_tpoZ6I-E5drZVtELc3Av-sPTqfgGjUf5DNsjGAvZ_jNCBj91tZ0o2XxNqcUCK3OccjQqNuePR5ColTTPo_M1cn0pFnYauhPxxz-hvI5JLGdfxk4cVK3B1FhEQ6LwQYe8zESw==]. Receptacles located on the dwelling including attached carports and attached garages are to be protected by a GFCI [strathcona](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHV8AaxwyWwVMBXe7wtBt0t2EGcnjsvry1BlUlz3pgxystNGp-S-6zZK68naFcXb9xislQi2b5OIR1aXi3MH2ibC7TdthCcXQmpn_vqf3rPwTS5TyAVZSJWjZ9s4bGhfNtPloitKjIr58Ay9J9SACFVBYfY8lPmxi_6h1PZT-alFxDqpr8N2qd3Vuggr-hq9HTlhwRzajnxoC71cGg=]. All receptacles (except for automobile heater receptacles) installed outdoors and within 2.5 m of a finished grade shall be protected by a ground fault circuit [strathcona](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHV8AaxwyWwVMBXe7wtBt0t2EGcnjsvry1BlUlz3pgxystNGp-S-6zZK68naFcXb9xislQi2b5OIR1aXi3MH2ibC7TdthCcXQmpn_vqf3rPwTS5TyAVZSJWjZ9s4bGhfNtPloitKjIr58Ay9J9SACFVBYfY8lPmxi_6h1PZT-alFxDqpr8N2qd3Vuggr-hq9HTlhwRzajnxoC71cGg=]. Attached garage receptacles need to be tamper-resistant and have arc-fault protection [strathcona](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHV8AaxwyWwVMBXe7wtBt0t2EGcnjsvry1BlUlz3pgxystNGp-S-6zZK68naFcXb9xislQi2b5OIR1aXi3MH2ibC7TdthCcXQmpn_vqf3rPwTS5TyAVZSJWjZ9s4bGhfNtPloitKjIr58Ay9J9SACFVBYfY8lPmxi_6h1PZT-alFxDqpr8N2qd3Vuggr-hq9HTlhwRzajnxoC71cGg=].

Keep in mind that local residential electrical codes can vary, so it's always best to confirm specific requirements with your local building permit department [thespruce](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDCWIOy6cxvblKtIpE9pONGHSz1cbaa__xWh4ixFWt8d1-ZztlJSRx2S-zR29B5DfSRmAc5MeqcTN3BSPodqwz6GQC_zNwsm35S-BtJ82hlm8sU_S2zeutUsVpix4fEletfjhxpBb3Wy304xIRnAFJSJdpEJrME0U=).
